\par\par
Windows Explorer is a decent entry-level file manager, capable of allowing even one's grandmother to become an instant file manager-ess. The point and click, drag & drop paradigm is very intuitive and gives access to immediate no-frills basic file management. However, for the more dedicated user who owns his/her computer for more than a month or two, and whose interactions with the machine extend beyond surfing the net, the fundamental cracks in the said explorer become apparent.\par
\par
Have you ever wished the standard Windows Explorer was a little bit more efficient for the day-to-day file management tasks? Are you longing for the functionality of older file managers but can't find one that is 32-bit compatible? Do you find some applications in the explorer replacement market a bit too taxing to setup and use? Then look no further, \b\i 2xExplorer\b0\i0  is the answer and twice as nice at that. It combines the user-friendliness of the standard Explorer with the increased efficiency and advanced features of good-old \b dual-pane\b0  file managers like \i Norton Commander\i0 . It is a package that will appeal to the power user, yet its similarity with Explorer will ensure that less experienced users will not be driven away either.\par
\par
2xExplorer is a fusion between the efficient dual-pane file management format of yesteryear and the intuitive tree/content pane format of modern operating systems. It aims to deliver the best of both worlds, without pledging allegiance to either of the two prototypes. You may regard it as an explorer on steroids, with an additional pane for browsing folder contents side to side. Apart for this extra pane, 2xExplorer fills in many glaring \i omissions\i0  in the windows Explorer:\par
\pard{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf4\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li360\b Filters\b0  (wildcard based) for limiting the files displayed in a contents pane, and for controlling the selection of items.\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Keyboard \b shortcuts\b0  for nearly all commands, an indispensable feature for efficient everyday use.\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Briefcase-beating lightweight folder \b synchronisation\b0  engine.\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Notepad-thrashing internal simple yet powerful text \b editor\b0  and RTF/Hex viewer.\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Improved Find Files tool offering more \i control\i0  over the search criteria.\par
\b\f1{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Printing\b0  of folder contents and other statistics.\f0\par
\lang1033{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Automatic Batch file (\f2 *.bat\f0 ) generation that can be used for delicate management operations, as the \b mass renaming\b0  of files.\lang2057\par
\f1{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}File and folder \b shreder\b0  (complete destruction).\f0\par
\f1{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}File \b split & merge\b0  commands.\f0\par
\f1{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Create \b hard links\b0  to files and folders (NTFS).\f0\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Complete file date information (modified \i plus\i0  created and last accessed) is both shown and used for various operations throughout the program.\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Proper sorting for file type using the filename extension alphanumerically; no more \f2 ".INI"\f0  files before \f2 ".BMP"\f0  ones like in the confused explorer.\par
\pard\par
2xExplorer offers a host of powerful commands found in heavyweight file managers like Norton Commander, yet it is not poised to reproduce faithfully the original item. The author makes no apology for departing from the traditional looks and modus operandi that some NC purists would regard compulsory for any file manager braving a comparison with the founder of the dual pane scene. For example, there seems to be little justification for two sets of toolbars (i.e. drive buttons, status bars, etc.) - one for each pane. Despite this external dissimilarity though, you'll soon realise that 2xExplorer is every bit as efficient, useable and addictive as NC. In fact it surpasses the master in providing all mod cons of an up to date 32-bit shell namespace browser:\par
\pard{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf4\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li360 Browsing and file management in \i non-filesystem\i0  folders like Control Panel, Desktop, \b zipfolders\b0  etc.\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Full \b drag/drop\b0  \lang1033 (including right-dragging) \lang2057 and shell \b context menu\b0  support.\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Multifunctional address bar for specifying folder names \i and\i0  visual filters\lang1033 , plus running (executing) DOS or windows programs\lang2057 .\par
\b{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Bookmarks\b0  and internet-style back/next folder navigation.\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Separable tree view; one can have \i both\i0  the tree view and the two contents panes visible at the same time.\par
\lang1033\b{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}Thumbnail\b0  previewer for many popular graphics formats (jpeg, gif, bmp, etc.)\lang2057\f1 , HTML and Office documents.\f0\par
